title: For Sale:  Re:  Question
postcontent: I don't know if it's inappropriate, but I think it's another step towards Political Correctness that is not only slightly ridiculous but gives the anti-gun folks ammo to attack us.  Just answer this question---how are you as an ordinary citizen going to check to see if a gun is stolen using a serial number?  The police are not not going to help you, because they can't---I had a gun stolen and asked the police for help---they told me that under current laws nobody except the dealer you bought from is required OR allowed to keep info regarding a firearm purchase past 2 weeks, and there is no state or local database maintained on stolen or missing firearms.  So you get a serial number---what are you going to do to make yourself feel all warm and fuzzy?  Google it?  I'm not trying to be funny or derisive, I'm just pointing out that there really is no mechanism for you to check, so you can waste the motion and energy but it won't prove anything.  Besides, laws have already proven that unless it can be proven that you KNOW that a firearm is stolen or that you're selling to someone who is prohibited from owning a firearm you can't be charged with a crime.  The worst that can happen is that someday, somewhere you could have to surrender a gun if through some weird circumstance an owner could prove it was stolen, ie insurance claim.  Other than that---knock yourself out, but it's not going to get you anywhere, and it might cost you a gun you want to buy or a buyer when you're looking to sell.  My $0.02 and my experience.
